procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for PK/PD analysis including plasma total Mo, PUF-Mo, Cu, LBC, and ceruloplasmin.

procedures.name: 24-hour Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Collection
procedures.description: Collection of all urine over a 24-hour period for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection

code.decode: Chromatography, quantitative, column (eg, gas liquid or HPLC); fecal analysis

procedures.label: Fecal Collection
procedures.description: Independent collection of individual fecal samples with record of date, time, and weight for copper and molybdenum analysis.

procedures.name: 12-lead ECG

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads

procedures.label: Electrocardiogram
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead electrocardiogram to evaluate heart rate and intervals (PR, QRS, QT, and QTc).

procedures.name: Physical Examination

code.decode: Office or other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of a new patient

procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: Full assessment of cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic/diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Testing

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy tests for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Excretion Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movement frequency and timing.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Device
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: Completely automated device for measuring blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Venous Cannula
medicalDevices.description: Placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws; not to be left in place longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Venous Catheter
medicalDevices.description: Used for venous access; must be flushed a minimum of every 8 hours.
